<br>
Only a few things really increase the size of money you're going to get, here they are:<br>
 - Tradeable high end items. Verant doesn't make a ton of these, except in dungeons with a crapload of lizardmen, and that zone isn't really the target of a raid anyhow.<br>
 - Plat. Plat comes from tradeable items or from selling stuff as a guild (Mqing armor for quests, or epic pieces). Guilds completely control that plat. If someone's got a crapload of plat, they either are a good trader, farmer, or scammer. It doesn't really relate to how a guild interacts with that person at all unless they are scamming the guild.<br>
 - Game altering items. Mage epic, for example. Fungus tunic. Items that give out mana pres, or flowing thought. The cash difference you get because you have 3-4 more flowing thought than if you didn't have that item is actually quite small. Shop around. The impact on price is much more focused on the plat you have than the no drop stuff you have.<br>
<br>
When I sold, I wasn't in a mad frenzy to try and score a few more items from EA. In fact, I don't think I even played more than a few hours (murdering people in the bazaar arena) in the last 2 weeks I owned the account.<br>
<br>
If you guilds are worried about people leaving the guild, focus on who you bring to the raids to begin with. If you're bringing an idiot or a thief, expect to have them screw things up or steal from you. Do your homework when you have an applicant. Instead of drooling over another person on raids, make joining a complicated process that only a refined, dedicated prospect can get through. CC has the right idea in this aspect. During the couple months I spent in EA, I saw more loot walk out the door via /guildremove than I anticipated. Your guild's recruitment policy -DEFINES- your attrition rate.<br>
<br>
People ebay because they don't want to play anymore and they don't feel an obligation to leave their account in the hands of their friends. Make your guildmates be friends who do not have a predisposition to ebay and solve the problem already. Or lose items. Either way works for me, I'll be converting soldiers into stains in UT2003. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uravendawn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RavenDawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/22/02 7:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25.topic&index=522>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Saal</span><hr size=1> Your gonna get waxed saal. Stay away from UT2k3 else ill find ya and slime yer ass. &gt;= ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showMessageRange?topicID=25.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showMessageRange?topicID=25.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showMessageRange?topicID=25.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showMessageRange?topicID=25.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showMessageRange?topicID=25.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showMessageRange?topicID=25.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm24.showMessageRange?topicID=25.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/f